values: Over the past week I'll go out and get my mail - mostly mass mailings and some cards and letters. The mail truck is gone. Then, three or more hours later I go outside only to find packages on the doorstep. This usually means that they are being delivered in the DARK. Not to mention that my cousin had a package delivered to the SIDE of her house. Not the porch, not anywhere near the door, but on the side. The only reason it was found was because her grandson tripped over it. While I appreciate the postal services zeal to deliver the goods, I can't help but think that there's a fundamental sorting problem going on.
So, alpha monsters of the week, leprechauns and fangirls can tell just by looking that Sam has no soul. But angels can't. That is so very sad on so many levels.
Off to have my eye surgery. Nothing says fun like an eye flap lifting and cell scraping. THIS WILL NOT HAPPEN AGAIN.

Aargh! I have skin cells growing between my eye flap and my eye. AGAIN. So, a second surgery is scheduled for Tuesday. Lifting the flap and 'scraping' away the cells seems to be the only option here. Which I find odd and frustrating. This damn well better work.
I can't believe I ran out of candy. I had over 50 kids; I usually get 15 to 20.
If you like zombies, don't miss tuning into Walking Dead on AMC next weekend. A tv series about a zombie apocalypse. What's not to like?
Has anyone's fandom ever had a Big Bang that *didn't* post all the stories at once? Isn't that the point? aka the bang?
At first, I didn't care that Big Bang Theory had moved to Thursdays, after all, I wasn't watching anything else at 9:30pm. But no, they moved it to 8pm - thanks for the conflict with Bones people!

An ad on craigslist wants you to go to their garage sale because they have "lots of womens close".

I despair.
wtf is it with an ask.com website that's invading livejournal? I've had to block the damn url to stop it redirecting me every time I click on a link.
A 13,000 word story does NOT need to be split into TWELVE parts, particularly when they are posted on a WEBSITE and not an lj and you're posting them all at once. Aaargh.

Somehow, God alone knows how, the screw that holds the shower door to the roller had come loose so the door was hitting the bottom of the tub while miraculously still in it's track. This, of course, happens to the outer door which means both doors have to come off. Fun times, people. Fun times. I now know how to install shower doors. Turns out, it isn't rocket science. Just heavy, scary, work with a lot of glass.
My external hard drive hit the floor with a resounding thud. Now, it won't even light up when plugged in, just makes a chugging sound. I'm doomed.

I'm reading this story I printed out; it's 37 pages long in Times New Roman 9 point. I like the idea of the story. However, there's a typo or just the plain wrong word usage nearly every other paragraph. The editor in me is correcting this as I go along but it really takes me out of the story. I want to like it, I really do but at this point I'm not sure I'll be finishing it.
I don't care what anyone says. June is the longest month in the year. It drags on forever. One more day. sheesh.
Oh no, I smell skunk wafting through the bedroom window. Please, oh please, let me NOT find a carcass in the backyard tomorrow.
I don't care if there are only 30 days - June is the longest god damn month of the year.
I really *hate* it when a director slowly pans the camera around, and around, and around, the action. For me, it turns the tv show into a radio play really fast or I'll gonna hurl.

The series finale of Saving Grace is now officially the worst series finale I've ever seen. It was nonsensical, rushed, desperately trying for emotion and only succeeding in stupid. If it were fanfic, I'd be shredding it.

DW confidential used the theme from House - drove me crazy the entire time they used it because I knew I knew it but couldn't figure it out. Once it stopped, it popped into my head. Of all things to use....
I dreamt that two abandoned wips I mistakenly started to read had been finished. Then I woke up. It's a cruel world.
Had a hard time taking yesterday's Dr. Who seriously because Stonehenge Apocalypse was too fresh in my head. Seriously, the robot head in Stonehenge had me snorting water. It wasn't pretty.

The neighbors behind me have a rooster. It crows at 5am, 6am, 7am and 8am. Also at 5pm and 6pm. Guess when I call the cops? My only saving grace is that the dispatcher can hear it. As this animal is illegal in my city, I hope that it'll be gone by the end of the week. I'm getting pretty tired.
And lo, the phrase: It was a robot head! enters SPN fandom.
Just a thought: How much privacy can you expect if you renew your wedding vows in a grocery store?

Supernatural's season finale can be summed up in three letters: wtf?

More later, maybe.

Bullies Target Obese Kids http://health.yahoo.com/news/healthday/bulliestargetobesekids.html
New research suggests that just being overweight increases the risk of being bullied.

This just in: The sky is blue. Gravity works. Fire is hot. Water is wet.

I'd like to sign up and get grant money for the above studies.

head, meet desk.

Tonight's Supernatural was brought to you by the word: BORING!

Wow. You guys managed to make the apocalypse dull and predictable. 

No love, Me.

One of Yahoo's news story's titled something like: One request Chelsea has for her Dad with the copy link reading: Bill Clinton reveals there's one thing his daughter wants from him before he walks her down the aisle.

All I can think is, "Please, Dad, don't fuck my bridesmaids!"
Well, two years in a row RuPaul's picked the person that I wasn't rooting for to win. sigh
Wouldn't it be great if <lj-cut> Missouri turned out to be God? </lj-cut>

So nice to see that Bones has toned down the product placement advertising from over the top blatant to oh look, here's a sponsor. I mean, a conversation about why Angela drives the car she does? *headdesk*

Dreamt that Cas, Dean and Sam were on RuPaul's Drag Race. I would pay to see this.

Also, wouldn't Cas and Dean work well in The African Queen?

Maybe I need more sleep.

Wow. I find it hard to believe that Numb3rs was tanking so badly in the ratings that CBS only committed to 16 episodes this year and that they're not picking it up for next year. Really? Off the top of my head, I can only think of one other CBS show I make it a point to watch and that's Criminal Minds. My Fridays will be network free after tomorrow.
Nothing makes me not read a story faster than the warning "non-linear story telling" coupled with a word count of less than 6,000. Thank you, no.
Am skimming the SGA auction. When an item says, "functionality is unverified" you can take that to mean that It Doesn't Work. Gotta love the spin.

I've been thinking about Supernatural lately. Hey, what else should I be doing? 

<lj-cut text="My thoughts this way">I don't buy that Dean has no hunger. In my opinion Dean's hunger is to avert the apocalypse -kill/imprison Lucifer. Like Famine's going to indulge that. Of course, Famine obviously didn't see Sam's desire for the same and so we have two Horsemen down. And, after this episode, I'm pretty damn sure I don't want to see what the powers that be have in mind for Pestilence.

Regarding the apocalypse as a whole, I believe that it's a test for the angels, one that they are failing miserably. Well, with one notable exception. And, if I'm lucky, Gabriel will get with Winchester's the program but I'm not holding my breath.

As for the whole: There's no free will. I say, "Bullshit". If everything is so damn predetermined then why are the angels trying so very, very, hard to make it happen? If all roads lead to the apocalypse then why not sit back and let it happen? Again, I think this is part of the angel's test.

Almost forgot. Castiel said that his vessel craved red meat. There are cases (go ahead, google) of organ donor recipients who start to crave things that their donors once loved. So, until Jimmy makes an appearance, I'll continue to believe that he's gone on to his reward.</lj-cut>
Winamp will streamlink one, and only one, program from the same site. It's very weird, annoying, and frustrating.
Holy crap. Just looked up "murals at Denver airport". That is some scary shit. Who approves these things?
Two bags of concrete, an 8 foot post for a 6 foot fence and two hours later, a new fencepost has been installed. Let's hope it dries before it rains. Really. Pray.
For some reason I'm reading every Supernatural/Criminal Minds crossover that I can find. So, far, it's not been a bad thing.

SyFy (stupid spelling) has canceled the SGU marathon for Christmas Day. http://www.gateworld.net/news/2009/12/syfy-cancels-sgu-christmas-day-marathon/ Could this mean that the shiny new show is really polished shit? And yes, Mythbusters proved you could do that!

Well, the new parts are in: the gas valve and the, er, fan unit. Also, a new, free thermostat which has, of course, a smaller footprint than the old one leaving 35 year old wallpaper showing but hey, I can paint a few square inches later.

Now. Should the heater fail again, I'll be getting a new one. I can say I'm not keen on that given the time it takes to install but that's what I'll be asking/demanding should the worse case happen. Had the parts not come in yesterday that's what would have happened per the store manager, Tamara. They were losing money sending someone out here each time as it was.

I was just looking at Creations' site and omg, almost every convention is for Twilight! I, I don't even want to contemplate what that would be like. And, while I can take vampires in almost any construction, I just can't fathom ones that sparkle. It's too Hello Kitty.
Thank you wolfshark and gillianinoz for the pretty snowflakes!

Got out of the post office today to discover that the person who parked next to me is so close to my car that I can't reach the door handle, forget getting in the vehicle. I go back inside and ask who owns the little red car. Older woman raises hand and I go over to explain the problem. She apologizes, leaves the line and out we go. Instead of simply moving the car over in the spot, she Leaves The Parking Lot. Dude. I think her family needs to check on her because she's either losing it or was too embarrassed (no, I wasn't loud or mean in the post office) to return.

I was kind of enjoying the new V - not fannishly mind you, but just as a non-offensive almost hour of tv. But it's not coming back until March. March. Seriously, four months. What? The writers can't figure out what's going to happen? The storylines suddenly went all sparkly? My hopes are not raised.
Let's see: woke up, snuggled with the cats, took an hour long walk with the neighbor, showered, ate breakfast, got on internet to check mail and, oh shit, it's almost three o'clock! Oops.
Day six with no heat; furnace to be replaced tomorrow because the company had a cancellation and could bump the delivery up a day. Go me. This one better last 20 years, too.
